This paper deals with the optimization of resource allocation and offloading in cellular networks, which is a topic that falls under the domain of network engineering and optimization. The paper specifically focuses on the downlink rate distribution in a two-tier cellular network, which involves the use of multiple access technologies and frequency bands. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). 

The paper also involves the use of mathematical modeling and optimization techniques to derive an optimal strategy for joint resource partitioning and offloading. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). 

Additionally, the paper discusses the use of interference avoidance techniques, which involves the use of signal processing and communication theory. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
